WEBVTT

00:10.076 --> 00:12.579
Hey, you're looking
a little under the weather.

00:12.579 --> 00:14.214
You all right?

00:14.214 --> 00:16.015
He most certainly is not.

00:16.015 --> 00:17.317
He dined on that
lovely can of bacon fat

00:17.317 --> 00:18.545
you've been hiding
under the sink.

00:18.752 --> 00:21.054
Aw, geez. Poor little guy.

00:21.054 --> 00:22.222
(doorbell rings)

00:22.222 --> 00:25.725
You know bacon grease
is bad for dogs.

00:25.725 --> 00:29.217
Ironic, considering its vast
health benefits for humans.

00:32.232 --> 00:33.722
Hello.
Hi, guys.
Hello.

00:34.234 --> 00:35.223
Hey.
Sorry
we're late.

00:35.735 --> 00:36.736
Well, that's all right.

00:36.736 --> 00:38.238
We're not having
lunch until 1 :1 5.

00:38.238 --> 00:39.739
Oh, great.

00:39.739 --> 00:41.604
Oh, long night, Niles?

00:42.042 --> 00:44.411
Oh, a bit. We were out
at a party last night.

00:44.411 --> 00:46.106
At Bill Gates' house.

00:48.081 --> 00:49.070
Really?

00:51.051 --> 00:54.354
Some sort of
charity event?

00:54.354 --> 00:57.050
Oh, no, just a few
people over for dinner.

00:58.358 --> 01:00.223
His wife has
been following

01:00.560 --> 01:02.118
Maris's case, and she
wanted to meet us.

01:04.129 --> 01:06.633
It seems the story's
captured everyone's imagination.

01:06.633 --> 01:08.134
People want to get
the inside scoop.

01:08.134 --> 01:09.536
Their house
is enormous.

01:09.536 --> 01:11.371
I got lost
going to the loo,

01:11.371 --> 01:14.272
but a voice in the wall
guided me back.

01:17.277 --> 01:18.778
Sounds like fun.

01:18.778 --> 01:19.767
Anyway, I thought
after lunch

01:20.280 --> 01:21.281
we might stop
by the museum

01:21.281 --> 01:22.782
for the Goya exhibit.

01:22.782 --> 01:24.284
Actually, we're going

01:24.284 --> 01:27.087
tomorrow night with
the Blenkinsops.

01:27.087 --> 01:28.721
Tomorrow? But...

01:28.721 --> 01:30.690
the museum's
closed tomorrow.

01:30.690 --> 01:33.318
Not for Bunny
and Bruce.

01:33.426 --> 01:36.196
Well. Oh.

01:36.196 --> 01:38.198
With all the rarefied elbows
you've been rubbing lately,

01:38.198 --> 01:40.200
I'm surprised you could
find the time for lunch

01:40.200 --> 01:41.201
with a commoner like me.

01:41.201 --> 01:43.829
Oh, now, stop, but if
we could get going,

01:44.337 --> 01:45.839
I have a perfume launch at 4:00.

01:45.839 --> 01:47.340
Oh.

01:47.340 --> 01:48.329
(doorbell ringing)

01:50.343 --> 01:53.847
It's a pretty lady
holding some mail.

01:53.847 --> 01:57.317
Oh, you didn't pull
that trick again, did you?

01:57.317 --> 01:59.285
I have no idea
what you're talking about.

01:59.686 --> 02:02.689
Step aside. Don't let her
slip it under the door.

02:02.689 --> 02:03.690
Hello.

02:03.690 --> 02:05.191
Hi. Sorry to disturb you.

02:05.191 --> 02:06.681
Some of your mail
got mixed in with mine.

02:07.193 --> 02:08.193
Oh, dear. How
did that happen?

02:08.193 --> 02:10.697
Some of it just seemed
to be jammed in there.

02:10.697 --> 02:12.198
Uh-huh.

02:12.198 --> 02:13.700
Really? Well, you know,

02:13.700 --> 02:15.702
we must make allowances
for our mailman.

02:15.702 --> 02:16.600
He's a veteran.

02:18.471 --> 02:19.873
So, uh...

02:19.873 --> 02:21.407
my name's Dr. Frasier Crane.

02:21.407 --> 02:22.876
Caroline Harwich.

02:22.876 --> 02:24.377
Nice to meet you,
and this is my family.

02:24.377 --> 02:25.366
My father, Martin Crane.

02:25.879 --> 02:26.379
Hi.

02:26.379 --> 02:27.380
My sister-in-law, Daphne,

02:27.380 --> 02:29.382
and my brother, Niles.

02:29.382 --> 02:31.384
You look awfully familiar.
Have we met?

02:31.384 --> 02:32.886
I am somewhat
of a media figure.

02:32.886 --> 02:34.387
No, your brother.

02:34.387 --> 02:37.379
Oh, you're Niles Crane
from that big murder case.

02:37.891 --> 02:39.256
I saw you on the news.

02:39.492 --> 02:41.561
Mmm. He's been on
three times this week.

02:41.561 --> 02:43.263
He's practically famous.

02:43.263 --> 02:45.565
Oh, well...
hardly famous.

02:45.565 --> 02:48.268
Yes, my brother doesn't like
to toot his own horn.

02:48.268 --> 02:51.271
You know, I was discussing that
very personality type today

02:51.271 --> 02:53.262
on my very popular radio show.

02:53.573 --> 02:55.268
Oh, right, right--
Dr. Frasier Crane.

02:55.575 --> 02:56.269
Yes.

02:56.576 --> 02:57.577
Yes, my mother listens to you.

02:57.577 --> 02:59.579
Oh.

02:59.579 --> 03:02.282
Well, anyway, it was
nice meeting you all.

03:02.282 --> 03:03.283
Yes, likewise.
Take care.
Bye-bye.

03:03.283 --> 03:05.285
Yes, bye.

03:05.285 --> 03:06.582
You know, isn't it nice to know

03:07.287 --> 03:08.922
there are still
honest people in the world?

03:08.922 --> 03:11.391
How come your mail
never gets mixed up

03:11.391 --> 03:12.759
with that sweaty
fat guy's upstairs?

03:12.759 --> 03:14.750
We should, we should
really be running along.

03:15.261 --> 03:16.763
Yes, yes, you know, I'm afraid

03:16.763 --> 03:18.253
we'll have to be
lunching at Vindaloo.

03:18.765 --> 03:19.766
I couldn't get us in
at le Toque.

03:19.766 --> 03:20.767
Mmm...

03:20.767 --> 03:22.200
Oh, n...

03:22.268 --> 03:23.836
Well, you know,
maybe I should call.

03:23.836 --> 03:26.339
I've had the best luck
with restaurants lately.

03:26.339 --> 03:29.342
Well, they swore that they were
absolutely booked solid.

03:29.342 --> 03:30.843
Oh, dear.

03:30.843 --> 03:32.345
Hello. Yes, wondering
if you could possibly

03:32.345 --> 03:34.336
squeeze in three
for lunch today?

03:34.847 --> 03:36.583
That's Dr. Crane.

03:36.583 --> 03:38.318
No, actually Niles.

03:38.318 --> 03:40.320
Oh, how lovely.
Thank you.

03:40.320 --> 03:41.378
We'll see
you in a bit.

